signatureAbility.signatureDescription: True legendary receivers make the impossible possible. When they enter the zone, they have greatly increased success rate on aggressive catches of 50+ yards regardless of coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running post and corner routes.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running streak routes.
RAC receivers fight for every possible yard after making a catch. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on RAC catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability have a high success rate when creating separation on the last cut of any route.
Aggressive receivers overpower defenders and attack the football. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their success rate on aggressive catches against single coverage.
Receivers with this ability run sharper routes and catch more consistently while running out and corner routes.
When in the red zone, receivers with this ability have a better chance to win contested catches against single coverage.
Some players thrive on making defenders look silly. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their fakeout rate on the next juke, spin or hurdle.
Passers with this ability are faster and more responsive to user input while scrambling behind the line of scrimmage.
Passers with this ability immediately respond to user input (and defenders react more slowly) on designed quarterback run plays.
Passers with this ability have a higher chance of completing a pass animation (and throwing the ball) while being sacked.
Ballcarriers with this ability have faster juke animations.
Defenders with this ability are rarely faked out by ballcarrier moves (and cannot be faked out when user-controlled).
Some players thrive on making defenders look silly. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their fakeout rate on the next juke, spin or hurdle.
Ballcarriers with this ability have more powerful stiff arm animations.
Blockers with this ability will frequently attempt and win pull blocks
